      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Your friend's experience is anecdotal, and anecdotal evidence is not a substitute for medical science, especially when dealing with blood clotting. Garlic oil and fermented greens are supplements, not precise pharmaceutical agents designed to manage anticoagulation levels. To truly achieve a \"gentle\" effect, you need a consistent, measured dose, which is what warfarin provides. If you are concerned about overmedication, you need to discuss adjusting your dosage with a physician who is willing to listen to your concerns, perhaps even seeking a second opinion from a specialist.",
